 Educational Background



 


St. Thomas University - Florida






 


Metropolitan State University

                  Metropolitan State University is a school in Saint Paul.                





 Career History



Senior Vice President & Chief Operating Officer

                                    2013 - Current                


Spirit Airlines, Inc.


                  Spirit Airlines empowers customers to save money on air travel by offering ultra low base fares with a range of optional services for a fee, allowing customers the freedom to choose only the extras they value. This innovative approach grows the traveling market and stimulates new economic activity while creating new jobs. Spirit's modern fleet, configuration and other innovations enable Spirit to burn less fuel per seat than competitors, making Spirit the most environmentally-friendly U.S. carrier. Spirit’s all-Airbus fleet currently operates flights throughout the U.S., Latin America and Caribbean.                




Chief Operating Officer

                                    2012 - 2013                


Frontier Airlines, Inc.


                  Frontier Airlines, Inc. provides airlines services. It offers passenger and freight transportation services such as seat assignment, electronic ticketing curbside check-in and online check-in services. The company was founded on July 5, 1994 and is headquartered in Denver, CO.                




President

                                    2008 - 2012                


Comair, Inc.


                  Comair, Inc. provides commercial aviation services. It operates through Delta Connection carrier, Delta Connection Academy in Orlando, Sanford, FL and Delta AirElite Business Jets in Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport. The company was founded in 1977 by David Mueller and is located in Erlanger, KY.                




President

                                    2006 - 2008                


Compass Airlines, Inc.


                  Compass Airlines received its FAA ATOS certification on April 5, 2007 and began commercial airline service on May 2, 2007. The business focus of the airline is to provide safe and reliable air transportation with great customer service through the operation of 36 new, state-of-the-art Embraer 175 aircraft that feature 12 first class seats and 64 main cabin seats. Customers love their aircraft's spacious interiors that are equipped with comfortable leather seats with adjustable head rests.                




Vice President-Base Maintenance Operations

                                    Prior                


Northwest Airlines Corp.


                  Northwest Airlines Corp. (NWA) provides air transportation services. It together with its subsidiaries engages in the business of transporting passengers and cargo. It has a fleet of about 450 aircrafts. It flies to more than 230 cities worldwide from hubs in Amsterdam, Detroit, Memphis, Minneapolis and Tokyo. Its domestic partners Pinnacle Airlines and Mesaba Airlines provide regional services to destinations under the Northwest Airlink banner. The carrier also has extensive alliances with Continental Airlines and Dutch airline KLM. It has joined SkyTeam, a marketing alliance led by Delta and Air France. Its principal subsidiaries are Northwest Airlines, Inc., MLT Vacations Inc. and Northwest PARS, Inc. It was founded in 1926 and is headquartered in Eagan, MN.                





 Public Holdings






